Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Suricata not capturing traffic

Verify network interface name: ip addr show
Check Suricata is running: sudo systemctl status suricata
Review logs: sudo tail -f /var/log/suricata/suricata.log
Ensure interface is in promiscuous mode: sudo ip link set eth0 promisc on
Issue: nftables rules not blocking traffic

Verify rules are loaded: sudo nft list ruleset
Check IP forwarding is enabled: cat /proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward
Review nftables logs: sudo journalctl -u nftables
Test with explicit drop rule: sudo nft add rule inet filter forward ip saddr 192.168.100.0/24 ip daddr 192.168.1.0/24 drop
Issue: Python scripts cannot read logs

Check file permissions: ls -l /var/log/suricata/eve.json
Add user to suricata group: sudo usermod -aG suricata $USER
Verify log file exists and is being written: sudo tail /var/log/suricata/eve.json
Issue: No alerts being generated

Update Suricata rules: sudo suricata-update
Verify custom rules syntax: sudo suricata -T -c /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml
Generate test traffic to trigger alerts
Check alert threshold settings in rules
